Rating: 4
This recipe is fantastic as others have noted. Due to time constraints, I omitted the olives but will add them next time. Also, I substituted a good quality balsamic for the red-wine vinegar because I sometimes find that red-wine vinegar can be too astringent and can ruin a dish rather than enhance it. I used a sourdough baguette, a bread with more texture and body than just a plain Italian or French baguette that has little substance. All in all, a keeper I will definitely make again!

Rating: 3
Very good recipe, and I'd definitely make it again. Although I think I'll leave out the olives next time, or at least put in less. They hijack the flavor of the dish when you get more than a one or two bits in any bite.

